# design noise

re_des_1= design_sheet.re_1_ex1.values
re_des_2 = design_sheet.re_1_ex2.values

re_des_1= -(re_des_1- design_sheet.re_1_ex1.values[-13])/design_sheet.re_1_ex1.values[-13]
re_des_2 = -(re_des_2 - design_sheet.re_1_ex2.values[-13])/design_sheet.re_1_ex2.values[-13]

re_var_des = np.var(np.vstack([re_des_1,re_des_2]).T, axis = 1)

In [12]:
noise_prior = gpytorch.priors.NormalPrior(0,1) # simple prior
lengthscale_prior = gpytorch.priors.GammaPrior(2, 0.5)
outputscale_prior = gpytorch.priors.GammaPrior(2, 0.1)

likelihood = gpytorch.likelihoods.GaussianLikelihood(noise_prior = noise_prior,
                                            noise_contraint = gpytorch.constraints.GreaterThan(1e-4))

covar_module = gpytorch.kernels.MaternKernel(nu = 2.5,
                                             lengthscale_prior = lengthscale_prior,
                                             lengthscale_constraint = gpytorch.constraints.GreaterThan(0.001))

covar_module = gpytorch.kernels.ScaleKernel(covar_module, outputscale_prior = outputscale_prior)
In [13]:
num_iter = []
tensor_list = []
Y_pred_list = []

for i in range(part):
    
    ind = np.array(a[i]).flatten()
    
    X_train = X[ind]
    Y_train = Y[ind]
    train_Yvar = Yvar[ind]
    
    gp = SingleTaskGP(X_train, Y_train, likelihood, covar_module = covar_module)
    
    mll = gpytorch.mlls.ExactMarginalLogLikelihood(gp.likelihood, gp)

    mll.train()
    gp.train()
    likelihood.train()
    
    #fit_gpytorch_mll(mll)
    fit_gpytorch_scipy(mll)

    mll.eval()
    likelihood.eval()
    
    UCB = UpperConfidenceBound(gp, beta=.2)
    
    candidate = optimize_acqf(
    UCB, 
    bounds=bounds, 
    q=1, 
    num_restarts=5, 
    raw_samples=20,
    )
    
    if candidate[1] > .5:
        
        num_iter.append(i)
        tensor_list.append(candidate[0][0].detach().numpy())
        Y_pred_list.append(candidate[1].detach().numpy())
    
        print(candidate[0][0], candidate[1])
    
tensor_list = np.array(tensor_list)

GP and SVR prediction¶

In [15]:
nat_y_gp = []
des_y_gp = []
nat_y_svr = []
des_y_svr = []

num_samples_to_select = int(len(nat_rm) * 0.8)
clf = svm.SVR(kernel='rbf')

for i in range(3):
    
    random.seed(i)
    selected_samples = random.sample(np.arange(len(nat_rm)).tolist(), num_samples_to_select)
    
    X_train = X[selected_samples]
    Y_train = Y[selected_samples]
    train_Yvar = Yvar[selected_samples]
    
    # SVR
    clf.fit(X_train, Y_train.flatten())

    y_pred_nat = clf.predict(X)
    y_pred_des = clf.predict(X_des)
    
    nat_y_svr.append(y_pred_nat)
    des_y_svr.append(y_pred_des)
    
    print('SVR %d finished!' %i+1)
    
    
    # GPR
    gp = SingleTaskGP(X_train, Y_train, likelihood, covar_module = covar_module)
    mll = gpytorch.mlls.ExactMarginalLogLikelihood(gp.likelihood, gp)

    mll.train()
    gp.train()
    likelihood.train()
    
    fit_gpytorch_scipy(mll)

    mll.eval()
    likelihood.eval()

    with torch.no_grad():
        posterior = mll.model.posterior(X)
        posterior_des = mll.model.posterior(X_des)
        
    nat_y_gp.append(posterior)
    des_y_gp.append(posterior_des)
    
    print('GPR %d finished!' %i+1)
